Cristina Mihaela Nicolescu","target":"Author/Cristina Mihaela Nicolescu","line":77},{"title":"Author/Cristina Mihaela Nicolescu","target":"Author/Cristina Mihaela Nicolescu","line":78},{"title":"Author/Ioana Daniela Dulamă","target":"Author/Ioana Daniela Dulamă","line":79},{"title":"Author/Ioana Daniela Dulama","target":"Author/Ioana Daniela Dulama","line":80},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/buruleanu_statistical_2018/buruleanu_statistical_2018.pdf","line":82}],"metadata":{"id":"buruleanu_statistical_2018","type":"article-journal","title":"Statistical Characterization of the Phytochemical Characteristics of Edible Mushroom Extracts","issued":{"date-parts":[[2018]]},"DOI":"10.1080/00032719.2017.1366499","container-title":"Analytical Letters","abstract":"ABSTRACTThe antioxidant activity, total phenolic content and total flavonoid content of ten edible mushrooms species, including cultivated (Pleurotus ostreatus, Agaricus bisporus white and brown) and wild (Pleurotus ostreatus, Macrolepiota procera, Cantharellus cibarius, Russula vesca, Russula alutacea, Boletus edulis and Agaricus campestris), were determined. The extraction was performed using water and 50% water – ethanol and the caps and stipe were investigated separately. Water was the most appropriate solvent for phenolic compounds regardless of the sample. On the contrary, the presence of ethanol in the solvent increased the extraction of flavonoids for cultivated Pleurotus ostreatus (caps and stipe), and wild Russula alutacea, Russula vesca, Agaricus campestris, Pleurotus ostreatus (only caps) and Cantharellus cibarius, Macrolepiota procera (only stipe). Significant differences between the antioxidant activities of the samples were registered in relationship with the different solvents. The antioxi...","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Buruleanu","given":"Lavinia","literal":""},{"family":"Buruleanu","given":"Lavinia","literal":""},{"family":"Buruleanu","given":"Lavinia Claudia","literal":""},{"family":"Rădulescu","given":"Cristiana","literal":""},{"family":"Radulescu","given":"Cristiana","literal":""},{"family":"Georgescu","given":"Andreea Antonia","literal":""},{"family":"Georgescu","given":"Andreea Antonia","literal":""},{"family":"Danet","given":"Florin Andrei","literal":""},{"family":"Danet","given":"Florin Andrei","literal":""},{"family":"Olteanu","given":"Radu Lucian","literal":""},{"family":"Olteanu","given":"Radu Lucian","literal":""},{"family":"Nicolescu","given":"Cristina Mihaela","literal":""},{"family":"Nicolescu","given":"Cristina Mihaela","literal":""},{"family":"Dulamă","given":"Ioana Daniela","literal":""},{"family":"Dulama","given":"Ioana Daniela","literal":""}],"citation-key":"buruleanu_statistical_2018","year":"2018","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Statistical Characterization of the Phytochemical Characteristics of Edible Mushroom Extracts"],"author-links":["[[Author/Lavinia Buruleanu]]","[[Author/Lavinia Buruleanu]]","[[Author/Lavinia Claudia Buruleanu]]","[[Author/Cristiana Rădulescu]]","[[Author/Cristiana Radulescu]]","[[Author/Andreea Antonia Georgescu]]","[[Author/Andreea Antonia Georgescu]]","[[Author/Florin Andrei Danet]]","[[Author/Florin Andrei Danet]]","[[Author/Radu Lucian Olteanu]]","[[Author/Radu Lucian Olteanu]]","[[Author/Cristina Mihaela Nicolescu]]","[[Author/Cristina Mihaela Nicolescu]]","[[Author/Ioana Daniela Dulamă]]","[[Author/Ioana Daniela Dulama]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/buruleanu_statistical_2018/buruleanu_statistical_2018.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"7quq4i","at":1774951894970}},"smart_blocks:Research/@buruleanu_statistical_2018.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[0.01347126,-0.04199532,-0.00269131,-0.06168311,0.0599093,-0.00647016,0.03162766,0.0293021,-0.01926025,-0.02124617,-0.0381064,-0.1089561,0.00421671,0.00213094,0.02898196,-0.00781521,0.04884766,0.0304348,